    "instruction": "Root cause summary: The single failure was caused by a sudden traffic surge originating at IG02. Root cause component: IG02. Root cause occurrence datetime: 2021-03-23 18:00:00+08:00 (Asia/Shanghai). Root cause reason: abrupt high incoming request/row_count spike from IG02 that overloaded downstream services (Tomcat02/03/04 and MG01/MG02), producing transient processing/latency increases and short GC/host metric disturbances downstream. Supporting evidence: earliest anomalous trace point is IG02 trace.to_Tomcat03.row_count > P95 at 2021-03-23 18:00:00+08:00, followed immediately by elevated trace row_count on Tomcats and latency spikes on MG02 and later Tomcat log row_count and GC pause anomalies. Recommended follow-ups: review IG02 traffic source/config to identify cause of spike (client traffic burst, misroute, or replay), consider rate-limiting/throttling at IG02, and inspect downstream autoscaling or queueing to mitigate similar spikes."
